#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Between 2021 and 2023 Tails, [Tor](https://torproject.org/), and the "
"[Guardian Project](https://guardianproject.info/) partnered to organize "
"training and usability tests in Ecuador, Mexico, and Brazil. Our goals were "
"to:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '- '
msgid ""
"Promote our digital security tools and train human rights defenders in the "
"Global South."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"- Learn from their experiences and needs to help us prioritize future work."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Improve the usability of our tools based on their feedback."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usability tests and improvements"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We conducted 4 rounds of in-person moderated usability tests in Mexico, "
"Brazil, and Ecuador to identify usability issues in the features of Tails "
"that are most important to new users:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid "- Tor Connection"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Persistent Storage"
msgid "- Persistent Storage"
msgstr "Archivio Persistente"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The DesignOps tools that we used to organize these usability tests are all "
"[[publicly available on our website|contribute/how/user_experience]]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The detailed methodology for each of the usability tests is explained in the "
"corresponding GitLab issues, linked below."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installation"
msgstr "Installazione"

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"In December 2021 in Mexico, we learned that the tools for new users to "
"install Tails worked well, but several people got lost while navigating the "
"instructions on the website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"Based on these findings, we restructured our installation pages and fixed 30 "
"usability issues on the website."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"We tested these improvements in August 2022 in Brazil and confirmed that the "
"new installation pages were much easier to follow. Only 1 out of 4 "
"participants had trouble installing Tails on their own. All participants "
"could start Tails and connect to the Tor network easily."
msgstr ""

